    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1421"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1421">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/323.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Spanish Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 12, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to inform you that
                    according to a telegram I have just received from the Spanish Consul at
                    Veracruz, ‘dated June 12, the Constitutionalists of Tampico are continuing to
                    impose enforced loans upon the Spaniards, and that upon the vouchers which they
                    give as a receipt of the sums collected, it is stated that these are a voluntary
                    contribution. Two Spanish subjects, Juan Isusi and Ramon Junco have been
                    arrested for refusing to contribute.</p>
                <p>I call your attention to this serious situation, in the hope that you will exert
                    your influence with the Constitutionalists to obtain the suspension of the order
                    imposing these enforced loans.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
